The software is intellectual property of the University of Bremen, Germany. You can freely redistritbute this software for non-comercial pruposes as long as 
(1) it includes a reference to the authors and
(2) all files are included. The files in this package are
    README          -- the readme file for SWORD
    LICENSE_MINISAT -- the license file for MiniSat, which is used as underlying SAT solver
    LICENSE_Smt2Sf  -- the license file for Smt2Sf, which is used as readin-routine for the QF_BV input laguage

    bin/sword       -- the SWORD solver
    
    lib/libsword.a  -- the SWORD library

    include/        -- all necessary header files: libsword.h, libmodule.h, SwordOpcode.h, SolverTypes.h
                       and one example module: modules/CardinalityLessThan.h

    doc/            -- a tutorial:            tutorial.pdf
                       two small examples:    example1.cpp example2.cpp
                       compile instructions:  USAGE, Makefile
                       

